<h2>Manage milestones</h2>

<p>Milestones track key deliverables and checkpoints in your project, helping you monitor progress and identify any risks or delays.</p>

<h3>Viewing milestones</h3>
<p>You can view all milestones for a project in a sortable table that shows:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Milestone name and description</li>
    <li>Status (complete, at risk, in progress, delayed)</li>
    <li>Due dates and actual completion dates</li>
    <li>Progress percentage</li>
    <li>Assigned owner</li>
</ul>
<p>To view milestones, navigate to your project and select <strong>Milestones</strong> from the project navigation menu.</p>

<h3>Adding a milestone</h3>
<p>To add a new milestone:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Milestones</strong> view for your project</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add milestone</strong></li>
    <li>Enter the milestone name and description</li>
    <li>Set the due date</li>
    <li>Optionally assign an owner</li>
    <li>Save the milestone</li>
</ol>

<h3>Updating milestones</h3>
<p>You can update milestone information at any time:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Click on a milestone to view detailed information</li>
    <li>Update the status, progress percentage, or completion date</li>
    <li>Add notes or updates about the milestone</li>
    <li>Change the assigned owner if needed</li>
</ul>

<h3>Milestone statuses</h3>
<p>Milestones can have the following statuses:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Not started:</strong> Milestone has been created but work hasn't begun</li>
    <li><strong>In progress:</strong> Work on the milestone is actively underway</li>
    <li><strong>At risk:</strong> There are concerns about meeting the milestone deadline</li>
    <li><strong>Delayed:</strong> The milestone is past its due date</li>
    <li><strong>Complete:</strong> The milestone has been successfully delivered</li>
</ul>

